arts.ttl: Mourinhoâ€™s Fenerbahce draws with Benfica, Bodo/Glimt wins big in Champions League playoffs 1st legs
arts.sum: Fenerbahce drew 0-0 at home against Benfica in the first leg of their qualifying playoff, despite the Portuguese team having a player sent off in the 71st minute. Seven playoffs will be decided with return games on Tuesday and Wednesday next week with the winners completing the 36-team Champions League lineup.

arts.ttl: Ten-man Benfica hold on for draw against Fenerbahce
arts.sum: Florentino Luis is sent off for a second yellow card in the 71st minute but Benfica manage to hold on to take a 0-0 draw back to Portugal for the second leg of their Champions League play-off against Fenerbahce.
